  "appearance": {
    "en": "Benzoic Acid occurs as white, crystals or crys-talline powder. It is odorless, or has a faint, benzaldehyde-like odor. It is freely soluble in ethanol (95), in acetone and in diethyl ether, soluble in hot water, and slightly soluble in water."
